WEBVTT

00:04.265 --> 00:05.353
Previously...

00:05.483 --> 00:08.660
You found your penicillin.

00:08.791 --> 00:11.141
No woman speaks to me like that.

00:11.272 --> 00:12.664
What have you done?

00:14.710 --> 00:16.146
Don't!

00:16.277 --> 00:18.192
Roger, you spoke.

00:18.322 --> 00:19.497
Whether ye're there to hear

00:19.628 --> 00:21.108
or even if my voice isn't able,

00:21.238 --> 00:22.935
I'll always sing for you.

00:23.066 --> 00:25.286
My husband's whiskey venture...

00:25.373 --> 00:28.158
Well, it's barely breaking even.

00:28.289 --> 00:31.553
But a partner
with the right connections...

00:31.683 --> 00:35.470
Mr. Bonnet will be
personally meeting
Mr. Alexander Malcolm,

00:35.600 --> 00:38.908
purveyor of the finest whiskey
in the Carolinas.

00:39.039 --> 00:41.519
Your men left because
you betrayed their trust.

00:41.650 --> 00:43.956
I made you a captain
without time to prepare you

00:44.087 --> 00:45.367
or teach you
what the word meant.

00:45.480 --> 00:47.351
He doesn't have any faith in me.

00:49.701 --> 00:51.747
♪ Sing me a song ♪

00:51.921 --> 00:54.619
♪ Of a lass that is gone ♪

00:54.793 --> 00:57.013
♪ Say, could that lass ♪

00:57.187 --> 01:00.103
♪ Be I? ♪

01:00.277 --> 01:02.366
♪ Merry of soul ♪

01:02.540 --> 01:05.239
♪ She sailed on a day ♪

01:05.413 --> 01:07.415
♪ Over the sea ♪

01:07.502 --> 01:10.592
♪ To Skye ♪

01:10.766 --> 01:13.464
♪ Billow and breeze ♪

01:13.638 --> 01:16.032
♪ Islands and seas ♪

01:16.206 --> 01:19.035
♪ Mountains of rain and sun ♪

01:19.209 --> 01:21.298
♪ Mountains of rain
and sun ♪

01:21.472 --> 01:23.953
♪ All that was good ♪

01:24.127 --> 01:26.260
♪ All that was fair ♪

01:26.434 --> 01:28.740
♪ All that was me ♪

01:28.914 --> 01:31.482
♪ Is gone ♪

01:31.656 --> 01:33.876
♪ Sing me a song ♪

01:34.050 --> 01:36.792
♪ Of a lass that is gone ♪

01:36.966 --> 01:38.707
♪ Say, could that lass ♪

01:38.881 --> 01:41.666
♪ Be I? ♪

01:41.840 --> 01:44.104
♪ Merry of soul ♪

01:44.191 --> 01:47.019
♪ She sailed on a day ♪

01:47.194 --> 01:51.589
♪ Over the sea ♪

01:51.763 --> 01:57.682
♪ To Skye ♪

02:00.642 --> 02:02.948
♪

02:03.035 --> 02:07.127
♪ Sing me a song ♪

02:07.301 --> 02:09.781
♪ Of a lass ♪

02:09.868 --> 02:12.828
♪ That is gone ♪

02:13.002 --> 02:17.311
♪ Say, could that lass ♪

02:17.485 --> 02:20.052
♪ Be I? ♪♪♪

02:20.227 --> 02:22.968
♪

02:27.669 --> 02:29.149
Well, the heartbeat
sounds strong.

02:37.461 --> 02:39.159
And baby's
in a perfect position.

02:39.246 --> 02:41.161
Any day now.

02:41.291 --> 02:43.250
You know, after two,

02:43.380 --> 02:45.097
you could probably deliver
this baby all by yourself.

02:45.121 --> 02:46.644
Maybe.

02:48.603 --> 02:51.171
It does make me feel better
that ye'll be here.

02:54.478 --> 02:58.743
Not so much as my physician,
but to share it with me...

02:58.874 --> 03:00.571
as a...

03:02.573 --> 03:03.574
As my ma.

03:06.577 --> 03:09.406
♪

03:13.236 --> 03:15.760
Time is marked and measured
in different ways.

03:15.934 --> 03:18.459
♪

03:18.589 --> 03:20.461
The colors of our lives
were changing.

03:20.635 --> 03:22.767
♪

03:22.854 --> 03:25.205
The vibrant greens
of summer faded

03:25.335 --> 03:28.556
beneath the ever-varied
canvas of sky,

03:28.686 --> 03:31.428
replaced by the russet tones
of autumn,

03:31.559 --> 03:33.561
brown hues of harvest,

03:33.691 --> 03:36.520
and blue-violet shades
of indigo dye.

03:36.607 --> 03:39.393
♪

04:02.590 --> 04:03.634
Dada.

04:05.854 --> 04:07.290
Shit.

04:07.421 --> 04:09.161
What?
What is it?

04:09.292 --> 04:11.033
Oh, something stung me.

04:14.428 --> 04:16.560
Mm, nasty sting you got there.

04:16.647 --> 04:19.041
Want me to blow on it?

04:19.171 --> 04:20.738
Ye are a sadist.

04:23.611 --> 04:25.700
You must get it
from your father.

04:25.830 --> 04:27.615
Shit.

04:29.225 --> 04:30.225
Hmm.

04:31.662 --> 04:33.751
What's this new word?

04:33.882 --> 04:35.362
Must have got that
from his father.

04:37.407 --> 04:38.756
Breakfast?

04:38.887 --> 04:41.106
Mm, yes, please.

04:41.193 --> 04:43.021
Eggs, please.

04:43.108 --> 04:44.458
And then I think Jemmy

04:44.588 --> 04:46.416
should go and see Lizzie
after breakfast.

04:46.547 --> 04:47.547
- Mm.
- Bree!

04:47.635 --> 04:49.114
Roger Mac, ye there?

04:50.725 --> 04:52.988
- Mm.
- Where else would we be?

04:53.075 --> 04:54.555
Coming!

04:57.819 --> 04:58.819
Move yourselves.

04:58.907 --> 05:00.256
No.

05:08.395 --> 05:10.310
- Come in.
- No time to be lazin' about.

05:10.440 --> 05:12.486
Josiah's seen signs of game
west of the...

05:14.183 --> 05:15.271
Ridge.

05:18.970 --> 05:22.887
Uh, meat is meat,
see us through the winter.

05:25.063 --> 05:26.456
Could do with a good marksman.

05:30.460 --> 05:33.289
Um, I'm supposed to be helping
dye the cloth today,

05:33.420 --> 05:35.378
and I have been
really looking forward to it.

05:35.509 --> 05:36.945
Roger will go with you.

05:41.297 --> 05:43.255
If ye're willing, Roger Mac,

05:43.386 --> 05:46.389
I need able-bodied men, and...

05:46.520 --> 05:47.782
able-bodied ye are.

05:50.828 --> 05:52.047
I'll wait outside.

06:00.621 --> 06:03.363
♪

06:22.730 --> 06:23.557
There.

06:23.687 --> 06:25.123
Yeah, very good, lad.

06:25.297 --> 06:27.865
♪

06:30.128 --> 06:31.652
'Tis no elk.

06:31.782 --> 06:33.523
They have very tall antlers.

06:35.612 --> 06:36.874
How will it be, Colonel?

06:37.005 --> 06:39.050
Well, the wind's blowing
from the west.

06:39.181 --> 06:41.181
We'll make our way down
to the bottom of the slope

06:41.270 --> 06:43.011
so they willna catch our scent.

06:43.141 --> 06:44.752
Spread out.

06:46.014 --> 06:48.582
Roger Mac and I will come
from behind and drive them
toward ye.

06:48.712 --> 06:50.540
We'll take what we can.

06:50.671 --> 06:53.238
Bring the horses.
Do what ye must.

06:53.369 --> 06:54.738
We'll meet back at the Ridge
at the end of the day.

06:54.762 --> 06:56.503
Very good.

06:56.677 --> 06:59.419
♪

07:12.954 --> 07:14.434
I'm no great tracker,

07:14.564 --> 07:16.174
but I've stepped
in enough of these

07:16.305 --> 07:18.046
to know a cow pat
when I see one.

07:18.176 --> 07:19.743
I hope we're not hunting cows.

07:19.874 --> 07:22.093
I'll be damned.

07:22.224 --> 07:24.618
Only three cows on the Ridge.
It's not one of them.

07:24.705 --> 07:25.923
It's still warm.

07:35.716 --> 07:36.978
♪

07:37.065 --> 07:38.849
Oh, my God.

07:38.936 --> 07:41.722
♪

07:50.382 --> 07:52.428
♪

08:01.524 --> 08:04.092
Go.
I must reload.

08:04.266 --> 08:06.921
♪

08:10.881 --> 08:12.622
Ah!

08:18.236 --> 08:19.716
♪

08:30.945 --> 08:33.164
A snake.

08:33.295 --> 08:35.427
Wee bugger bit me on the leg.

08:35.602 --> 08:37.647
♪

08:37.734 --> 08:39.301
Come and sit down.
Let's have a look.

08:42.957 --> 08:44.306
Where is it?

08:44.480 --> 08:46.395
♪

08:49.093 --> 08:51.922
♪

08:53.663 --> 08:54.663
I think it's venomous.

08:57.101 --> 08:58.541
I'll have to cut it,
drain the poison

08:58.668 --> 09:00.148
by sucking it out.

09:00.235 --> 09:02.150
♪

09:02.280 --> 09:03.280
Wait.

09:04.718 --> 09:06.589
Claire does this

09:06.720 --> 09:09.461
before she sets herself
to cut someone.

09:09.636 --> 09:12.421
♪

09:16.033 --> 09:17.861
All right, go on, then.

09:18.035 --> 09:20.821
♪

09:28.132 --> 09:30.004
Again.
Quick, for God's sake.

09:32.006 --> 09:35.009
Aah!

09:41.450 --> 09:44.235
Enough!

09:44.366 --> 09:46.455
Ye'll drain me dry.

09:49.458 --> 09:52.374
♪

09:54.332 --> 09:56.944
♪

09:57.074 --> 09:59.599
I've made more of a mess
than the snake did.

10:03.864 --> 10:05.648
♪

10:05.735 --> 10:07.563
Oh, there's no sign of anyone.

10:07.694 --> 10:08.999
Can ye walk?

10:09.173 --> 10:12.002
♪

10:16.877 --> 10:19.880
♪

10:20.010 --> 10:21.359
Go find the others.

10:21.533 --> 10:24.406
♪

10:27.235 --> 10:30.064
♪

10:38.681 --> 10:41.466
♪

10:42.859 --> 10:45.645
♪

10:50.171 --> 10:51.955
'Tis a good day for dyeing.

10:53.957 --> 10:55.655
I hope you mean
the cloth, Lizzie.

10:55.785 --> 10:57.395
- It sounds so ominous.
- Aye.

11:05.490 --> 11:07.623
Did you always know
you wanted to be a doctor?

11:07.754 --> 11:10.670
No.

11:10.800 --> 11:13.803
Never really allowed myself
to dream of such a career.

11:15.109 --> 11:18.112
It wasn't easily available
to women when I was your age.

11:18.242 --> 11:19.722
And then being a nurse,

11:19.853 --> 11:22.072
that was about as much
as I could have hoped for.

11:22.203 --> 11:25.423
You seemed pretty single-minded
about it later on, though.

11:25.554 --> 11:28.426
Well, I had to be determined.

11:28.557 --> 11:30.157
No one was going
to open the door for me.

11:31.691 --> 11:33.170
But if you're lucky enough

11:33.301 --> 11:34.713
to know what it is
that you're meant to be...

11:34.737 --> 11:36.739
What if you don't know?

11:36.870 --> 11:39.960
Or if you do know,
but you just can't do it?

11:42.484 --> 11:45.400
Well, for most people...

11:45.530 --> 11:48.446
life as they find it
is often the life they lead.

11:50.840 --> 11:53.277
Now, is this about Roger...

11:53.408 --> 11:54.714
or you?

11:54.844 --> 11:56.846
Both.

11:56.977 --> 11:59.719
We talked about maybe teaching
here at the Ridge.

11:59.849 --> 12:01.068
It just made me think

12:01.198 --> 12:02.852
about how I can't apply
my calling here.

12:05.115 --> 12:08.553
Oh, sometimes it's doctor,
healer, a witch...

12:10.642 --> 12:12.819
But I'm not afraid
of what they call me,

12:12.949 --> 12:15.473
'cause that's what
I was born to be

12:15.604 --> 12:17.258
and will be till I die.

12:18.955 --> 12:22.959
Uh, if I were to lose you...

12:23.090 --> 12:26.180
or Jamie,
I would never be quite whole.

12:28.225 --> 12:29.749
But I would always have
that left.

12:31.881 --> 12:34.579
You're an engineer, Bree.

12:34.666 --> 12:38.105
And whatever it is
they call that here...

12:38.235 --> 12:40.368
you just have to find a way
to be that.

12:43.240 --> 12:45.677
And what about Da?
Does he know what he is?

12:45.808 --> 12:48.028
Oh, he knows.

12:48.158 --> 12:50.595
A laird?
Is that what you call him?

12:50.726 --> 12:52.902
Is he content with that?

12:53.033 --> 12:57.559
A laird, a husband, father...

12:59.082 --> 13:00.388
Those are no small things to be.

13:04.087 --> 13:06.742
Be patient.

13:06.873 --> 13:09.266
If going back to our time
isn't a possibility,

13:09.397 --> 13:11.921
Roger will find his purpose...

13:14.010 --> 13:15.403
And so will you.

13:15.490 --> 13:18.362
♪

13:28.590 --> 13:31.419
♪

13:49.132 --> 13:52.005
♪

13:59.403 --> 14:02.842
♪

14:14.810 --> 14:17.639
♪

14:40.967 --> 14:42.055
They're back.

14:51.629 --> 14:54.067
- How did you do?
- No luck.

14:54.154 --> 14:55.938
Nothing at all?

14:56.025 --> 14:57.940
We followed a small herd
of buffalo,

14:58.071 --> 15:00.391
but they moved off more quickly
than we thought they might.

15:04.033 --> 15:06.340
Did Uncle Jamie manage
to find anything
on his way back?

15:06.470 --> 15:08.037
No, they haven't returned yet.

15:08.168 --> 15:10.126
We thought they were with you.

15:10.213 --> 15:12.172
How far did you go?

15:12.302 --> 15:14.411
To the other side of the Ridge,
near the boundary of your land.

15:14.435 --> 15:16.393
We got separated in the hunt.

15:16.480 --> 15:18.700
We said we'd meet here
come dusk.

15:18.787 --> 15:20.920
Maybe milord decided
to make camp.

15:35.630 --> 15:38.502
♪

15:48.251 --> 15:51.037
♪

15:54.388 --> 15:56.520
Fair is fair.

15:56.694 --> 15:59.436
♪

16:08.010 --> 16:09.881
No sign of the men, then?

16:10.012 --> 16:11.013
No.

16:12.884 --> 16:15.670
But perhaps they'll see
the smoke from our fire.

16:20.153 --> 16:21.850
How are ye?

16:23.852 --> 16:26.681
Well.

16:26.811 --> 16:28.117
Well enough.

16:28.248 --> 16:29.771
Are ye sure?

16:29.901 --> 16:32.513
I have pins and needles
in my fingers,

16:32.643 --> 16:34.123
and my lips are numb.

16:44.307 --> 16:46.483
Is it usual, d'ye ken?

16:46.570 --> 16:48.130
Have you been drinking
too much whiskey?

16:49.312 --> 16:51.532
No, I thought I might
need that more later.

16:56.667 --> 16:59.714
And what would they do
in yer time for a snakebite?

16:59.844 --> 17:02.325
They'd inject you with
something called antivenom.

17:04.197 --> 17:05.850
A venom to battle the venom.

17:05.937 --> 17:07.287
In a way, aye.

17:08.897 --> 17:09.898
Here.

17:19.777 --> 17:21.997
Get some rest.
We'll leave at first light.

17:31.963 --> 17:34.792
♪

17:43.192 --> 17:45.194
- R-Roger?
- I'm here.

17:46.543 --> 17:48.632
D'ye ken the last rites?

17:50.199 --> 17:51.287
No.

17:53.463 --> 17:54.701
Ye won't be needing them anyway.

17:54.725 --> 17:55.944
Ye're not going to die.

17:56.031 --> 17:58.033
We both read that obituary.

17:58.164 --> 18:02.255
Aye, I'm to burn in a fire,
but...

18:02.385 --> 18:05.084
I feel I'm... I'm burning up
as we speak, Roger Mac.

18:06.998 --> 18:09.914
I know a prayer for the sick.

18:10.045 --> 18:12.395
And before you ask,
no, it's not in Latin.

18:15.050 --> 18:17.357
Try to get some more rest.

18:17.487 --> 18:18.487
Roger...

18:21.578 --> 18:22.927
Ye must kill Stephen Bonnet.

18:24.929 --> 18:26.235
If I canna, you must do it.

18:26.409 --> 18:28.455
♪

18:28.542 --> 18:29.542
He's alive.

18:29.630 --> 18:31.936
I know.

18:32.067 --> 18:34.348
Brianna overheard you
and Lord John talking
at the wedding.

18:37.203 --> 18:39.509
♪

18:39.640 --> 18:42.556
There's a man...

18:42.686 --> 18:44.993
Philip Wylie,
indebted to me yet.

18:45.124 --> 18:47.343
He's arranged for Bonnet
to smuggle my whiskey

18:47.474 --> 18:48.910
if-if Bonnet agrees to a meeting.

18:50.520 --> 18:51.913
Lord John kens the particulars.

18:54.133 --> 18:55.675
I don't know if I could take
another man's life...

18:55.699 --> 18:58.180
♪

18:58.311 --> 18:59.810
Even one who's done
what Bonnet has done.

18:59.834 --> 19:01.401
Ye must.

19:06.101 --> 19:08.364
If I canna do it, ye must.

19:08.495 --> 19:12.281
Claire told me yer father,

19:12.412 --> 19:16.329
Jeremiah, fought in
the second Great War.

19:16.459 --> 19:18.809
Ye would have, too,
if ye'd been of age.

19:18.940 --> 19:21.638
Aye, I suppose,
but that's different.

19:24.685 --> 19:26.925
When a man is standing there
before you, flesh and blood,

19:26.991 --> 19:28.036
with fear in his eyes...

19:28.123 --> 19:29.733
Bonnet stood before me once.

19:31.779 --> 19:34.999
I saved him from his
rightful fate at the gallows.

19:35.130 --> 19:37.698
He murdered my friend...

19:37.828 --> 19:39.569
attacked my wife...

19:39.656 --> 19:42.050
♪

19:42.181 --> 19:43.573
And Bree, he...

19:43.747 --> 19:46.533
♪

19:46.663 --> 19:49.666
If I hadna done that...

19:49.797 --> 19:53.540
But ye did, and it's done.
Ye can't change it.

19:53.670 --> 19:56.934
Perhaps this is my penance.

19:57.065 --> 20:00.373
Unfortunately for you...

20:00.503 --> 20:04.594
the son must pay for the sins
of the father...

20:04.725 --> 20:05.813
for my mistakes.

20:05.900 --> 20:07.989
♪

20:08.119 --> 20:09.164
You must do this.

20:09.251 --> 20:12.559
♪

20:12.689 --> 20:15.039
It's a hell of a time
to get philosophical.

20:15.170 --> 20:16.476
No time like the present.

20:16.650 --> 20:18.782
♪

20:18.913 --> 20:20.393
And ye're
a university professor...

20:22.438 --> 20:23.918
Or so everyone keeps telling me.

20:32.796 --> 20:35.625
♪

20:37.584 --> 20:42.241
If-if I'm to die tonight,
Roger Mac...

20:42.371 --> 20:44.852
promise me ye'll look
after Claire and the Ridge.

20:44.982 --> 20:46.549
Nonsense.

20:46.680 --> 20:48.240
We don't have to worry
about any of this

20:48.290 --> 20:49.639
because ye're going to live.

20:49.726 --> 20:52.512
♪

20:56.820 --> 21:00.259
It's a dangerous path
to go down... vengeance.

21:00.389 --> 21:03.479
Jocasta bequeathed River Run
to yer son.

21:05.612 --> 21:08.876
Bonnet has waged a war on us.

21:09.006 --> 21:12.227
We're defending our family,
our beliefs,

21:12.358 --> 21:14.795
those that come after us... wee Jemmy.

21:16.231 --> 21:17.885
I have reason to believe

21:18.015 --> 21:20.670
Bonnet will try to claim
yer son as his own.

21:20.801 --> 21:23.020
He'll have witnesses from the tavern

21:23.151 --> 21:26.110
Bree was willing to lay with him...

21:26.197 --> 21:27.851
for a silver ring.

21:33.248 --> 21:36.469
"But whosoever shall offend
those little ones

21:36.599 --> 21:38.993
"who believe in me,
better for him

21:39.123 --> 21:41.212
"that a millstone were hanged
about his neck

21:41.343 --> 21:43.303
and that he were drowned
in the depth of the sea."

21:43.389 --> 21:46.043
Matthew... chapter 18, verse 3.

21:46.174 --> 21:48.089
Verse 6.

21:52.398 --> 21:54.617
♪

21:54.748 --> 21:57.707
Bonnet's crimes are
unforgivable.

21:57.838 --> 22:00.144
Better we rid this earth of him,

22:00.231 --> 22:03.844
that he may never harm another being.

22:03.974 --> 22:06.760
There's a fine line
between a monster and a hero.

22:06.847 --> 22:09.806
♪

22:13.549 --> 22:17.510
Ye're here
because of yer love for Bree.

22:19.120 --> 22:20.774
She wouldna be alive

22:20.904 --> 22:23.516
if Claire and I hadna
changed things.

22:25.822 --> 22:27.982
Even though I blamed you
for hesitating to come back...

22:29.609 --> 22:30.697
I'm glad ye're here.

22:32.568 --> 22:35.397
I have to have faith
the Lord has a plan.

22:35.528 --> 22:38.531
If you want me to face Bonnet,

22:38.618 --> 22:40.924
you're gonna have to teach me
to fight.

22:41.055 --> 22:43.231
Roger Mac...

22:44.798 --> 22:46.452
I will...

22:46.582 --> 22:47.582
if I live.

22:47.627 --> 22:50.412
♪

23:14.871 --> 23:16.656
♪

23:17.918 --> 23:19.789
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

23:19.876 --> 23:22.662
♪

23:35.718 --> 23:39.505
What is this,
the bed of Procrustes?

23:42.769 --> 23:44.858
Well, it could be worse...

23:44.988 --> 23:47.513
could be Charon's boat.

23:47.643 --> 23:49.863
Ah, if I go to hell, I'm...

23:49.993 --> 23:51.473
glad ye're coming with me.

23:53.432 --> 23:57.174
Well, thankfully, you have not
lost yer sense of humor.

23:57.261 --> 23:59.655
God, I'm not even sure
what direction I'm going.

24:01.788 --> 24:02.788
Stop.

24:07.707 --> 24:09.186
What's wrong?

24:09.317 --> 24:12.363
Nothing that isna already wrong.

24:12.494 --> 24:15.018
Look up, Roger Mac.

24:17.325 --> 24:19.414
The wind's blowing from the west.

24:19.545 --> 24:21.198
Follow it home.

24:29.598 --> 24:33.297
If I die, Claire must leave.

24:33.428 --> 24:35.561
Send her, make her go.

24:35.735 --> 24:37.606
♪

24:37.737 --> 24:39.782
Ye should all go,

24:39.913 --> 24:42.611
if the bairn can pass
through the stones.

24:42.698 --> 24:45.266
It's not safe you here
without me.

24:47.790 --> 24:49.488
Tell Bree I'm glad of her.

24:51.577 --> 24:54.231
Give my... sword to the bairn.

24:57.191 --> 24:59.715
And tell Claire I... I meant...

24:59.846 --> 25:01.108
I meant it.

25:01.195 --> 25:04.024
♪

25:11.597 --> 25:13.686
Almighty God, out
of the depths, I cry to You.

25:15.688 --> 25:17.603
Lord, hear my voice,
don't let this man die.

25:17.777 --> 25:20.519
♪

25:25.436 --> 25:27.438
Lord have mercy.

25:27.613 --> 25:30.398
♪

25:37.797 --> 25:40.539
♪

25:44.020 --> 25:46.806
♪

25:55.989 --> 25:56.989
Roger!

25:58.339 --> 25:59.645
Uncle Jamie!

25:59.819 --> 26:02.561
♪

26:04.214 --> 26:07.000
Roger!
Uncle Jamie!

26:07.130 --> 26:08.305
Roger?

26:08.479 --> 26:10.481
♪

26:15.356 --> 26:18.664
♪

26:18.794 --> 26:20.535
Uncle Jamie!

26:20.709 --> 26:23.712
♪

26:23.843 --> 26:25.845
- Roger!
- Hello.

26:30.153 --> 26:33.504
♪

26:33.635 --> 26:34.680
Over here!

26:37.204 --> 26:38.292
Over here!

26:38.379 --> 26:39.510
♪

26:42.165 --> 26:44.080
Uncle Jamie!

26:44.211 --> 26:45.386
Roger!

26:51.522 --> 26:53.524
Hiya.
Come on.

26:53.699 --> 26:56.527
♪

27:04.187 --> 27:06.102
♪

27:13.544 --> 27:14.894
Rollo?

27:21.074 --> 27:22.075
Roger!

27:22.162 --> 27:25.295
♪

27:25.426 --> 27:26.775
He was bitten by a snake.

27:26.949 --> 27:29.735
♪

27:31.301 --> 27:32.607
Let's get him on the horse.

27:32.781 --> 27:35.262
♪

27:38.657 --> 27:40.833
I've never seen
anything like it before.

27:42.661 --> 27:44.501
Dinna tell me ye don't have
snakes in yer time.

27:46.055 --> 27:47.753
Yes, but...

27:47.883 --> 27:49.842
you wouldn't
usually call a surgeon

27:49.929 --> 27:51.757
about a snakebite.

27:51.844 --> 27:54.455
The closest thing
I've come to is...

27:54.542 --> 27:56.370
when a man got bitten
by a king cobra,

27:56.500 --> 27:58.764
my friend invited me
to watch the autopsy.

27:58.894 --> 27:59.894
Autopsy?

28:02.419 --> 28:04.987
What ye did to Leith Farrish?

28:06.859 --> 28:08.948
You like you've been
roasted over a spit.

28:09.078 --> 28:11.013
You should work on
your bedside manner, Sassenach.

28:11.037 --> 28:13.082
Bree...

28:13.213 --> 28:14.475
you stay with your father.

28:16.477 --> 28:17.696
Marsali.

28:21.351 --> 28:23.329
What will we do?
D'ye have something
ye can give him?

28:23.353 --> 28:25.051
I'm going to need you to get

28:25.138 --> 28:27.053
everyone to look
for some maggots...

28:27.183 --> 28:28.489
to eat the dead flesh.

28:28.619 --> 28:30.099
It should help
stave off infection.

28:30.186 --> 28:31.186
Tell me...

28:32.319 --> 28:33.319
Is it bad?

28:34.408 --> 28:35.539
Yes.

28:35.670 --> 28:37.411
Can ye cut it out?

28:37.541 --> 28:39.935
No, the venom's in his blood,

28:40.066 --> 28:41.589
and his body
will have to fight it.

28:41.720 --> 28:43.678
I'll make an onion poultice.

28:43.765 --> 28:45.549
That should help
clean the wound.

28:45.680 --> 28:47.508
I'll give him some
of the penicillin broth.

28:47.638 --> 28:49.423
Though...

28:49.553 --> 28:51.991
I'm not sure
how potent it'll be
if I give it to him orally.

28:52.078 --> 28:54.515
Damn yer needle be broken.

28:54.645 --> 28:57.561
Roger said Jamie was vomiting.

28:57.692 --> 28:59.389
That seems to have stopped.

28:59.520 --> 29:01.565
And Fergus said that he was
making snide remarks

29:01.696 --> 29:03.045
about the sled Roger made.

29:03.132 --> 29:04.394
Those are good signs.

29:04.525 --> 29:05.569
Yes.

29:07.658 --> 29:09.486
But if his leg turns
gangrenous, then...

29:09.617 --> 29:11.619
Then...

29:11.706 --> 29:13.752
I'll have the whole Ridge
out looking for maggots.

29:18.495 --> 29:21.281
♪

29:31.204 --> 29:33.946
♪

29:37.036 --> 29:39.778
♪

29:45.827 --> 29:48.351
Did, uh, any of the men take
a buffalo?

29:48.482 --> 29:50.701
I do ken I shot one.

29:50.832 --> 29:51.964
No.

29:52.094 --> 29:54.183
They came back empty-handed.

29:54.270 --> 29:56.011
Huh.
- Josiah won't stop
berating himself

29:56.142 --> 29:57.360
for letting them get away.

30:03.062 --> 30:05.194
Penicillin broth.

30:06.587 --> 30:08.913
Lucky for you, this doesn't
have to get injected
into your bum.

30:08.937 --> 30:10.896
Aye, good.

30:10.983 --> 30:13.115
I've had enough of yer needles
for one lifetime.

30:20.122 --> 30:21.682
Is there anything else
I can do to help?

30:30.611 --> 30:33.440
Marsali has everyone out
looking for maggots.

30:33.570 --> 30:35.224
I'm sure she could do with some help.

30:41.274 --> 30:44.016
♪

30:51.806 --> 30:53.373
You feeling any better?

30:53.460 --> 30:56.724
Huh...

30:56.855 --> 30:58.769
I thought I was,
but now I'm not so sure.

30:58.900 --> 30:59.901
Why?

31:01.772 --> 31:03.513
It's only...

31:06.342 --> 31:07.953
When you scold me like a magpie,

31:08.083 --> 31:09.780
I k-ken I'm gonna be all right.

31:11.652 --> 31:13.828
And when ye're tender as milk...

31:15.395 --> 31:16.875
Ye havena called me
any wicked names

31:17.005 --> 31:18.789
or uttered any words of reproach

31:18.877 --> 31:20.313
since I came home, Sassenach.

31:23.272 --> 31:24.621
Does this mean ye think
I'm dying?

31:24.752 --> 31:26.014
Fine.

31:27.450 --> 31:28.669
You fool...

31:28.799 --> 31:30.105
Stepping on a snake.

31:32.064 --> 31:33.674
Why didn't you look
where you were going?

31:33.804 --> 31:35.545
Ah, not while

31:35.676 --> 31:37.393
ch-chasing a thousand-weight
of meat downhill.

31:37.417 --> 31:40.115
You scared the hell out of me.

31:40.246 --> 31:42.378
Ye think
I wasna frightened, too?

31:42.509 --> 31:45.381
You are not allowed.

31:45.512 --> 31:49.037
Only one of us gets to be
frightened at any time.

31:49.124 --> 31:50.691
Right now it's my turn.

31:53.824 --> 31:56.566
♪

31:59.700 --> 32:02.529
♪

32:10.711 --> 32:13.627
♪

32:16.717 --> 32:19.546
♪

32:23.942 --> 32:25.378
What on earth are doing up?

32:28.033 --> 32:30.383
♪

32:30.513 --> 32:32.187
I ken what ye're thinking,
and I willna have it.

32:32.211 --> 32:34.430
I'm not gonna die,
and I dinna wish

32:34.561 --> 32:37.694
to live my life with half a leg.

32:37.825 --> 32:40.175
I've a horror of it.

32:40.306 --> 32:42.569
I'm not too keen
on the idea either, but...

32:42.743 --> 32:45.311
♪

32:45.441 --> 32:48.227
If it's a choice
between your leg
and your life...

32:48.357 --> 32:49.750
It's not.

32:49.924 --> 32:52.971
♪

32:53.101 --> 32:54.537
Jamie, it may be.

32:54.624 --> 32:56.626
- It won't.
- Fine.

32:56.757 --> 32:58.977
Just give me the bloody thing,
and I'll put it away.

33:00.369 --> 33:01.369
Yer word.

33:02.981 --> 33:04.634
- My what?
- Yer word.

33:06.332 --> 33:07.724
I may be fevered
and lose my wits.

33:07.855 --> 33:09.291
Not if ye to take my leg

33:09.378 --> 33:10.989
and not be in a state
to stop it.

33:13.034 --> 33:15.341
If you're in that state...

33:15.471 --> 33:17.038
then I won't have a choice.

33:17.125 --> 33:19.823
Perhaps you won't, but I-I do.

33:21.738 --> 33:23.349
And I've made it.

33:26.439 --> 33:29.181
♪

33:30.617 --> 33:31.617
Nothing.

33:33.750 --> 33:35.187
I'm looking for dead rabbits.

33:38.277 --> 33:40.540
Hey...

33:40.670 --> 33:43.412
you did everything you could.

33:43.543 --> 33:44.805
Here.

33:49.027 --> 33:51.681
I was hoping that
if I got him home
to Claire in time...

33:51.812 --> 33:53.770
He'll be fine.

33:53.857 --> 33:55.468
He's too stubborn not to be.

34:04.129 --> 34:06.087
Is there something else?

34:06.174 --> 34:08.394
If the worst should happen,
he wants me to go

34:08.524 --> 34:10.004
to a place
called Wylie's Landing.

34:10.091 --> 34:11.658
For what?

34:11.788 --> 34:13.529
A plan has been put into motion

34:13.616 --> 34:16.663
to find and kill Stephen Bonnet.

34:16.750 --> 34:19.579
♪

34:26.325 --> 34:28.370
Yer Da thinks Bonnet

34:28.501 --> 34:30.381
could have the right
to take Jemmy away from us.

34:30.503 --> 34:33.245
♪

34:34.463 --> 34:36.335
He attacked me.

34:36.422 --> 34:39.077
Well, people of this time see
the child as proof that...

34:40.991 --> 34:42.776
That you were
a willing participant,

34:42.906 --> 34:44.517
because God
wouldna allow a child

34:44.647 --> 34:45.692
to be conceived through...

34:45.866 --> 34:47.824
♪

34:47.955 --> 34:49.696
Rape.

34:49.826 --> 34:51.480
You're Jemmy's father.

34:51.611 --> 34:54.309
We were married already.
Doesn't the law protect you?

34:54.440 --> 34:56.529
We were alone
when we handfasted.

34:56.659 --> 34:58.618
There were a hundred witnesses
at our wedding

34:58.748 --> 35:00.315
after Jemmy was born.

35:00.446 --> 35:02.143
Possession is 9/10 of the law.

35:02.274 --> 35:04.841
I don't think
the law means much
to a man like Bonnet.

35:05.015 --> 35:07.627
♪

35:09.846 --> 35:11.152
Say something.

35:11.283 --> 35:13.285
Let's just find
these damn maggots.

35:13.415 --> 35:14.721
There's nothing dead here.

35:14.895 --> 35:17.724
♪

35:31.259 --> 35:34.088
♪

35:36.743 --> 35:38.005
Found some!

35:38.136 --> 35:40.181
Ooh, here we go.

35:40.312 --> 35:43.706
Oh, dinna fuss, baby.

35:43.837 --> 35:46.274
Hey, we'll go in in a second,
once I've got these in.

35:47.884 --> 35:48.972
Here we...

35:52.062 --> 35:53.760
♪

35:57.111 --> 35:59.200
♪

36:02.464 --> 36:03.987
Hey!
Here, here!

36:04.118 --> 36:06.033
Come over here!

36:06.164 --> 36:07.034
Here, here.

36:07.165 --> 36:08.383
Here.

36:08.514 --> 36:10.342
Come on, this way.
Come here, here.

36:10.472 --> 36:12.126
Here. Come on.

36:12.257 --> 36:14.302
Yeah, come on.
Here!

36:14.389 --> 36:15.999
Come on, follow me.

36:18.263 --> 36:19.916
Here.
Over here, come on.

36:20.047 --> 36:21.831
Come on, come on!

36:21.918 --> 36:23.050
This way, come on.

36:23.137 --> 36:24.486
Come on, come on.

36:24.617 --> 36:25.444
Come on.

36:25.618 --> 36:27.010
♪

36:27.097 --> 36:28.097
Bree!

36:39.109 --> 36:42.025
- Oh, shh, shh, shh, shh.
- Ow.

36:48.510 --> 36:51.687
Aah!

36:54.299 --> 36:57.040
♪

36:57.171 --> 37:00.392
What in God's name
were you thinking?

37:05.832 --> 37:08.226
Josiah found these in a dead...

37:10.793 --> 37:12.882
Never mind.
Uh, we have some.

37:13.013 --> 37:14.362
That's all that matters.

37:14.493 --> 37:15.755
Great.
Thank you.

37:22.544 --> 37:23.806
How is it, man?

37:23.937 --> 37:25.634
I'll do.

37:25.721 --> 37:27.549
Oh, these suckers won't hurt.

37:27.680 --> 37:29.247
They'll tickle
something fierce, mate.

37:32.119 --> 37:34.252
He's a great comfort...

37:34.382 --> 37:36.384
that Roger Mac.

37:38.995 --> 37:41.824
♪

37:45.741 --> 37:48.178
♪

37:51.138 --> 37:53.575
♪

37:53.662 --> 37:54.837
Be honest.

37:55.011 --> 37:57.840
♪

38:02.149 --> 38:04.630
His body's defeating the venom.

38:04.760 --> 38:07.067
But the infection in his leg...

38:08.764 --> 38:09.765
It's bad.

38:11.985 --> 38:14.596
It's too deep for the maggots
to make any difference.

38:14.727 --> 38:17.338
If only I had a way
of getting penicillin

38:17.425 --> 38:18.861
into his bloodstream, but...

38:19.035 --> 38:21.603
♪

38:22.822 --> 38:25.694
♪

38:32.397 --> 38:33.789
Roger Mac.

38:35.182 --> 38:37.532
Aye.
Do you need something?

38:40.492 --> 38:43.233
I wish to sleep in my own bed.

38:43.408 --> 38:46.149
♪

38:47.412 --> 38:49.588
Um...

38:49.762 --> 38:52.504
♪

38:58.466 --> 39:00.729
Ferrying you about is becoming
an everyday occurrence.

39:00.903 --> 39:03.689
♪

39:05.647 --> 39:08.433
♪

39:14.874 --> 39:18.704
God, the thought
of amputating...

39:18.834 --> 39:20.009
just makes me sick.

39:23.796 --> 39:26.102
Can't we just wait
a little bit longer

39:26.233 --> 39:27.974
and see if the maggots
take effect?

39:28.148 --> 39:30.977
♪

39:32.892 --> 39:34.217
But if there isn't
any improvement,

39:34.241 --> 39:35.634
then I don't have a choice.

39:35.808 --> 39:38.898
♪

39:39.028 --> 39:42.162
Except that he made me promise
that I wouldn't do it.

39:42.292 --> 39:44.164
At least he'll be alive
to be mad at you.

39:44.338 --> 39:47.602
♪

39:47.733 --> 39:50.170
Except every time
that he would look down,

39:50.257 --> 39:52.390
it'll be
a constant reminder that...

39:54.653 --> 39:57.569
That I was the one
who did it to him...

39:57.699 --> 39:59.527
that I didn't keep my word.

39:59.701 --> 40:02.487
♪

40:06.316 --> 40:07.535
Come help me!

40:09.798 --> 40:11.017
Come.

40:12.932 --> 40:14.194
Where are you moving him?

40:14.324 --> 40:16.065
To his bedroom.

40:16.196 --> 40:17.719
Why?

40:17.850 --> 40:20.896
I want to be in my own bed.

40:21.027 --> 40:23.899
But surely you should listen
to Auntie Claire.

40:24.030 --> 40:26.859
Stay there so she can heal
your leg properly.

40:30.732 --> 40:33.605
She thinks the only way
to do that...

40:33.735 --> 40:35.781
is by taking it off.

40:38.392 --> 40:40.786
Come on.

40:40.873 --> 40:42.875
And what good would I be
with only one leg?

40:44.920 --> 40:48.315
Well, did ye ever say that
to my father or to Fergus?

40:48.446 --> 40:52.493
Fergus was but a-a wee lad
when he lost his hand.

40:57.629 --> 40:59.065
And what difference
does that make?

41:02.503 --> 41:06.246
He and yer father are
far more courageous than me.

41:06.376 --> 41:08.509
Or not as proud or as stubborn.

41:12.644 --> 41:15.647
They're still the same.
It's still them.

41:15.777 --> 41:17.736
It is a matter of honor.

41:17.866 --> 41:20.260
They lost hand and leg
in battle.

41:20.347 --> 41:22.547
There's nothing honorable
about being bitten by a snake.

41:25.221 --> 41:26.788
Maybe I should go.

41:26.919 --> 41:29.225
No, stay.

41:29.356 --> 41:31.489
I want someone else
to hear this.

41:31.619 --> 41:33.403
You know, there were times
I felt guilty

41:33.491 --> 41:35.536
when I was younger
for wishing you were my father.

41:35.667 --> 41:38.321
I admired you so much,

41:38.452 --> 41:40.889
I ran away to Edinburgh
to be with ye.

41:43.109 --> 41:45.415
But ye're right.

41:45.546 --> 41:48.897
Now I do see how courageous
my father was and is.

41:49.071 --> 41:51.552
♪

41:51.683 --> 41:54.816
I never thought I'd see the day
I'd be ashamed of you, Uncle.

41:54.990 --> 41:57.776
♪

42:03.782 --> 42:06.524
♪

42:26.065 --> 42:28.110
What on earth is going on?

42:28.241 --> 42:30.112
I, um...

42:32.637 --> 42:34.595
I'm just gonna go
and see about a thing.

42:47.913 --> 42:49.523
I had to move, Sassenach,
because...

42:51.699 --> 42:56.095
I willna have you sleeping
in the surgery or on the floor.

42:56.225 --> 42:58.488
Ye'll sleep with me.

43:04.538 --> 43:07.367
♪

43:14.896 --> 43:16.202
What is it?

43:16.332 --> 43:18.160
It's nothing.

43:18.291 --> 43:20.380
Oh, you're a terrible liar.

43:22.295 --> 43:25.254
We were just talking about you
is all, Roger and I,

43:25.385 --> 43:27.145
saying it would be a shame
if you had left Marsali

43:27.169 --> 43:30.259
and walked all the way here
to see Uncle Jamie,

43:30.390 --> 43:32.958
because he's tired.

43:33.088 --> 43:35.438
But I did walk all the way
out here to see him,

43:35.569 --> 43:37.527
and I did leave Marsali.

43:37.658 --> 43:39.268
So I'll go and see him quickly.

43:39.399 --> 43:41.619
I think he's resting.
Maybe wait until later.

43:41.749 --> 43:45.579
What is it?
Where is he?

43:46.711 --> 43:48.340
Auntie Claire thinks she might
have to amputate if...

43:48.364 --> 43:49.627
If it gets worse.

43:51.324 --> 43:52.891
Why don't you want me
to see him?

43:52.978 --> 43:54.196
You don't think I can take it?

43:54.327 --> 43:57.635
No, I ken you can, but...

43:57.722 --> 43:59.288
I'm not so sure about him.

43:59.375 --> 44:01.116
He's stubborn.

44:01.247 --> 44:04.163
He doesna want to lose his leg.

44:04.250 --> 44:06.010
He's acting like it's
the worst possible thing

44:06.034 --> 44:08.384
that can happen to a man, and...

44:08.515 --> 44:10.299
well, I didna want
you to be upset.

44:10.430 --> 44:12.562
In one stroke, he's going
to be a man of leisure.

44:12.693 --> 44:15.478
What?

44:15.609 --> 44:19.308
It's what I told him
when it happened to me...

44:19.439 --> 44:21.591
that I would depend upon him,
and he would be there for me.

44:21.615 --> 44:23.530
It was our agreement,

44:23.661 --> 44:27.099
if I lost an ear or a hand
in his service.

44:27.229 --> 44:29.275
I was teasing him.

44:31.799 --> 44:34.628
"Man of leisure," eh?

44:34.759 --> 44:37.199
Well, I can't wait to hear what
Marsali has to say about that.

44:37.239 --> 44:38.980
Oh, I'm sure she'll have
plenty to say.

44:39.067 --> 44:40.707
She's seen what it's like
to live with me.

44:42.288 --> 44:43.811
You know...

44:45.683 --> 44:47.946
Marsali and I try not to think
about what we lack

44:48.076 --> 44:49.687
but about what we have.

44:49.817 --> 44:53.342
You and I have a father
and an uncle.

44:53.473 --> 44:56.911
We should be there for him
when he needs us.

44:56.998 --> 44:59.218
That's all we can do.

45:02.177 --> 45:04.614
♪

45:06.138 --> 45:08.836
♪

45:16.278 --> 45:17.323
Sassenach.

45:17.497 --> 45:20.326
♪

45:21.936 --> 45:22.936
What?

45:25.374 --> 45:26.549
Sleep beside me.

45:30.945 --> 45:32.381
Okay.

45:35.297 --> 45:38.126
♪

45:45.264 --> 45:46.656
How do you feel?

45:49.137 --> 45:52.140
Like a pile of moldy tripe...

45:54.664 --> 45:56.101
With maggots.

45:59.539 --> 46:02.150
You'd laugh on your deathbed,
wouldn't you?

46:02.324 --> 46:05.153
♪

46:11.725 --> 46:13.379
Does it hurt much?

46:15.120 --> 46:16.338
No.

46:18.601 --> 46:19.907
Just feel tired.

46:19.994 --> 46:22.780
♪

46:24.694 --> 46:25.913
It's no wonder you do.

46:26.087 --> 46:28.873
♪

46:33.399 --> 46:34.399
Dinna leave me.

46:34.530 --> 46:37.316
♪

46:39.927 --> 46:41.407
I could never leave you.

46:41.581 --> 46:44.410
♪

46:46.064 --> 46:48.893
I'm cold...

46:49.023 --> 46:50.198
Sassenach.

46:50.372 --> 46:53.245
♪

46:53.332 --> 46:55.638
Touch me.

46:55.769 --> 46:57.553
Touch me before I sleep.

46:57.727 --> 47:00.556
♪

47:00.687 --> 47:01.993
Jamie.

47:03.908 --> 47:04.908
Jamie.

47:04.952 --> 47:07.781
♪

47:11.045 --> 47:13.091
Jamie.

47:13.178 --> 47:16.224
No, no, no, no.
You stay with me.

47:16.398 --> 47:18.574
♪

47:21.577 --> 47:24.319
♪

47:26.147 --> 47:28.497
No. No.

47:28.584 --> 47:30.412
Here, I'm here.

47:32.240 --> 47:33.285
No, don't leave me.

47:33.372 --> 47:35.853
♪

47:35.983 --> 47:37.463
You're not leaving me.

47:37.637 --> 47:40.118
♪

47:42.120 --> 47:43.425
Oh, stay with me.

47:43.599 --> 47:45.514
♪

47:45.645 --> 47:46.951
I'm right here.

47:47.125 --> 47:49.910
♪

47:57.787 --> 48:00.529
That's it, yeah.

48:00.660 --> 48:03.315
Okay.

48:03.402 --> 48:06.274
♪

48:49.535 --> 48:51.102
Ye gave me yer word.

48:53.060 --> 48:54.888
Now I'm giving it back.

48:58.065 --> 49:01.590
When the time comes...

49:01.721 --> 49:03.505
ye may take my leg.

49:03.679 --> 49:06.508
♪

49:12.210 --> 49:14.647
I don't know why I even took it.

49:14.734 --> 49:18.346
Just felt compelled,
for some reason.

49:18.477 --> 49:21.132
I thought maybe if Claire knew the
species, it might help.

49:23.090 --> 49:24.439
It's stupid, really.

49:26.528 --> 49:28.704
Wait.

49:28.835 --> 49:29.923
Don't.

49:33.057 --> 49:35.537
♪ ♪

49:35.668 --> 49:36.668
Smell it.

49:45.417 --> 49:48.072
Okay? Better?

49:48.202 --> 49:50.291
This one, you can pick it up.

49:50.422 --> 49:52.380
Yeah, pick one.
Touch it, just...

49:52.511 --> 49:54.165
This one, pick it up.
Pick it up.

49:54.295 --> 49:56.558
- Fergus.
- Pick it up.

49:56.689 --> 49:58.473
- Fergus.
- What is it?

50:07.091 --> 50:08.491
Uh, I'll go fetch milady,
all right?

50:08.527 --> 50:09.528
There's no time.

50:09.658 --> 50:11.399
Oh, this one's not waiting.

50:13.314 --> 50:14.707
Oh! Ye're not going anywhere!

50:18.450 --> 50:19.929
I'm here.

50:26.501 --> 50:27.807
Here.

50:27.981 --> 50:30.940
♪

50:31.071 --> 50:33.508
Where the hell is everyone?

50:33.595 --> 50:35.138
I need more than one pair
of hands for this.

50:35.162 --> 50:37.860
♪

50:37.991 --> 50:41.560
When it's done,
take the leg and bury it...

50:43.388 --> 50:44.998
And never tell me where it is.

50:45.129 --> 50:46.652
I'm sorry, Uncle.

50:46.739 --> 50:48.480
I didna mean
what I said to you before.

50:48.610 --> 50:52.179
Aye, ye did.
You meant it.

50:52.310 --> 50:54.877
You were right to say it.

50:55.008 --> 50:56.140
It's all right.

50:56.314 --> 50:58.968
♪

51:06.976 --> 51:08.674
We're ready...

51:08.804 --> 51:11.329
I suppose.

51:11.503 --> 51:14.071
♪

51:17.465 --> 51:20.860
If you're inclined to pray...

51:20.947 --> 51:22.905
then now would be a good time.

51:25.517 --> 51:28.302
♪

51:36.005 --> 51:37.050
You'll need this.

51:37.224 --> 51:40.053
♪

51:46.059 --> 51:48.714
♪

51:59.072 --> 52:01.118
Wait.

52:01.205 --> 52:04.512
Did you know that pit vipers
have beautiful engineering?

52:04.643 --> 52:06.993
Their fangs are connected
to a venom sac in their cheek.

52:07.080 --> 52:09.537
So when they bite down,
the cheek muscles squeeze
the venom out of the sac,

52:09.561 --> 52:12.955
down through the fang
and into their prey.

52:13.086 --> 52:15.393
- What?
- Mama, their fangs are hollow.

52:15.567 --> 52:18.396
♪

52:18.483 --> 52:22.878
Jesus H. Roosevelt Christ.
You made a syringe.

52:23.009 --> 52:24.924
Is that the same snake?

52:25.054 --> 52:26.404
Fair's fair.

52:26.578 --> 52:29.320
♪

52:52.081 --> 52:53.431
Brace yourself.

52:53.605 --> 52:56.085
♪

53:00.264 --> 53:02.527
♪

53:09.098 --> 53:10.491
Beautiful engineering indeed.

53:10.665 --> 53:13.668
♪

53:15.279 --> 53:17.890
♪

53:35.037 --> 53:39.085
I'm so sorry I missed
your arrival.

53:39.216 --> 53:42.567
But I'm very happy
that you're healthy and safe.

53:45.396 --> 53:47.049
We're going to call her
Félicité.

53:47.180 --> 53:48.573
Oh.

53:48.703 --> 53:49.791
It's beautiful.

53:49.965 --> 53:52.751
♪

54:09.724 --> 54:12.510
I wanted to wait to be sure
ye were fine before I, um...

54:15.774 --> 54:18.733
Well, I'd like to point out
that you are, in fact, alive.

54:18.864 --> 54:20.561
Hmm.

54:20.692 --> 54:22.737
I didna think ye'd be one
to gloat...

54:25.262 --> 54:26.262
Professor.

54:29.048 --> 54:32.269
I wasn't gonna pass up
this opportunity.

54:32.399 --> 54:33.835
I may never get another one.

54:33.966 --> 54:34.966
Hmm.

54:36.316 --> 54:37.316
I want you to know...

54:40.364 --> 54:44.890
You are no longer
under any obligation to...

54:45.020 --> 54:46.805
fulfill my dying wish.

54:46.892 --> 54:47.936
I know.

54:50.243 --> 54:53.072
♪

54:55.770 --> 54:58.382
But I still want to go
with you to Wylie's Landing.

54:58.556 --> 55:01.298
♪

55:03.169 --> 55:06.128
I want to be there when you...

55:06.259 --> 55:07.913
meet Stephen Bonnet.

55:08.000 --> 55:10.829
♪

55:24.582 --> 55:27.324
♪

55:45.690 --> 55:47.518
You tried to die on me,
didn't you?

55:50.695 --> 55:53.872
That's why you had Roger
and Ian bring you in here.

55:57.484 --> 55:59.486
Yeah, it wouldn't have taken
much effort.

56:01.749 --> 56:02.881
And not dying was harder.

56:04.709 --> 56:05.579
Jamie.

56:05.710 --> 56:06.841
Aye.

56:08.974 --> 56:12.369
I may have resigned myself
to die,

56:12.456 --> 56:14.283
but that was...

56:14.414 --> 56:17.722
that was
before I made my choice.

56:17.852 --> 56:21.378
When I realized
my heart was slowing,

56:21.465 --> 56:23.989
the pain was growing
further away...

56:26.731 --> 56:28.994
The fever faded from both body
and mind,

56:29.124 --> 56:30.387
leaving the mind clear.

56:32.911 --> 56:34.478
I saw it...

56:34.608 --> 56:36.393
Saw what?

56:45.097 --> 56:47.491
I-it wasn't a-a door exactly,

56:47.621 --> 56:50.972
more of a passageway
of some kind.

56:51.059 --> 56:53.888
And I could go through it
if I wanted,

56:54.019 --> 56:55.803
and I did want to.

56:58.937 --> 57:00.634
I knew what lay behind me, too.

57:03.332 --> 57:06.379
I realized at that moment,
I had a choice...

57:09.077 --> 57:12.864
Go forward or turn back.

57:12.994 --> 57:15.432
And that's when you asked me
to touch you?

57:17.869 --> 57:20.306
♪

57:20.437 --> 57:24.353
I knew ye were the one thing
that could bring me back.

57:24.528 --> 57:27.356
♪

57:28.923 --> 57:31.056
So why did you choose to stay?

57:32.927 --> 57:35.582
'Cause ye need me.

57:35.669 --> 57:37.802
♪

57:37.932 --> 57:40.065
But not because you love me?

57:41.762 --> 57:44.591
Whether I'm dead... or you...

57:46.506 --> 57:48.552
Whether we're together
or apart...

57:48.726 --> 57:50.902
♪

57:51.032 --> 57:52.817
I will always love you.

57:54.993 --> 57:57.343
There's a war coming.

57:57.474 --> 58:00.868
God has made me what I am.
He's given me a duty.

58:01.042 --> 58:03.131
♪

58:03.218 --> 58:05.351
And I must do it...

58:05.482 --> 58:06.874
no matter the cost.

58:07.048 --> 58:10.182
♪

58:10.312 --> 58:12.576
Well, whatever the reason...

58:14.360 --> 58:17.755
James Fraser,
you made the wise choice.

58:17.929 --> 58:20.627
♪
